les\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"sustained dominance\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"over a decade\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"thedegreeto\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She does not win by tenths or even a single point but by multiple points.\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tenths\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"even a single point\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple points\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the U.S. Olympic trials,she won by over 5 points, the rough equivalent of nearly six falls.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1821, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S. Olympic trials\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"over 5 points\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"the rough equivalent\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1800}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly six falls\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Theoretically, this means Biles could have fallen half a dozen times and still beat the2020 Olympic champion, Sunisa Lee.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1853}, {\"ngram\": \"the2020\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic champion\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles is truly in a league of her own.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"a league\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But how is this possible?\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer is simple.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The answer\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles performs some of the hardest skills in the world and continues to complete increasingly harder ones, including some that no one else can do.\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2038}, {\"ngram\": \"the hardest skills\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"increasingly harder ones\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles' difficulty puts on her on a completely differently level; a new starting point means a new end point.\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2288, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles' difficulty\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"a completely differently level\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2243}, {\"ngram\": \"a new starting point\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"a new end point\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, under the current scoring system, she's rewarded for it.\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2351, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the current scoring system\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amajor 2006 changeto the gymnastics scoring system has allowed for and encouraged athletes to push for difficulty.\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Amajor\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"the gymnastics scoring system\", \"from\": 2374, \"t